</i></p><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The Institute of Health Visiting (iHV) is critical in promoting public health and well-being across the United Kingdom. This esteemed organisation supports the professional development of health visitors, ensuring they have the knowledge and skills necessary to deliver high-quality care to families and communities. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune will explore the iHV's role, highlight key facts and statistics, define essential terms, and discuss best practices for implementing relevant legislation and regulations. </span>
</p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-adc4" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-kYHfwS doYKjf pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hAcGzb cVhebe"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-21_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Understanding the impact of health visiting is crucial. Here are some key statistics that underscore the importance of this field:

















</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-23_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-24_ pf-text-1">Approximately 8,000 health visitors in the UK are responsible for around 250 children under five years old.

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-26_ pf-text-1">Health visiting interventions have been shown to reduce hospital admissions by 22% for children under five.&nbsp;</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-28_ pf-text-1">A study by the University of Kent found that health visitors contribute to a 12% reduction in postnatal depression rates among new mothers.


 














</li></ul><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-30_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">These statistics highlight health visitors' significant role in promoting health and preventing illness in communities.


















</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-32_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-33_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-34_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-36_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To fully appreciate the role of the IHV, it's essential to understand some key terms:

















</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-38_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health visitor</strong> - A registered nurse or midwife with additional training in community public health, focusing on preventative care for families with young children.

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-41_ pf-text-1"><strong>Institute of Health Visiting (IHV) </strong>- A professional organisation supporting health visitors through education, research, and advocacy to improve public health outcomes.

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-43_ pf-text-1"><strong>Public health</strong> - The science and practice of protecting and improving the health of people and their communities through preventive measures, health education, and policy-making.


</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-45_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-46_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-47_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices for implementing legislation and regulations
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-49_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Health visitors operate within a framework of legislation and guidelines that ensure the delivery of safe and effective care. Best practices include:


















</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-51_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong> Adhering to regulatory standards</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-53_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Health visitors must comply with standards set by regulatory bodies such as the Nursing and Midwifery Council (NMC). The NMC’s code outlines professional standards and behaviour, ensuring accountability and consistency in care.


















</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-55_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Ongoing professional development</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-57_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Continuous professional development (CPD) is crucial for health visitors. The iHV offers a range of training programmes and resources to keep health visitors up-to-date with the latest research and practices. This commitment to lifelong learning ensures that health visitors can provide high-quality, evidence-based care.


















</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-59_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Utilising evidence-based practices</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-61_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The iHV emphasises the importance of evidence-based practice. Health visitors are encouraged to utilise research and data to inform their interventions, ensuring they are delivering the most effective care possible. The iHV’s research initiatives provide valuable insights and resources to support this practice.



















</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-63_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Collaborative working</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-65_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Health visitors often work in multidisciplinary teams, collaborating with other healthcare professionals to provide comprehensive care. Effective collaboration ensures that families receive holistic support, addressing all aspects of their health and well-being.




















</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-67_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-68_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-69_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-71_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To maximise the impact of health visiting and the support provided by the iHV, we recommend the following:



















</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-73_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-74_ pf-text-1"><strong>Invest in CPD</strong> - Health visitors should regularly engage in CPD activities offered by the iHV to stay informed about the latest developments in the field.






</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-76_ pf-text-1"><strong>Promote awareness</strong> - Increasing public awareness of the vital role of health visitors can help garner support for their work and ensure families access the services they need.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-78_ pf-text-1"><strong>Support research</strong> - Continued investment in health visiting research is essential. Policymakers and healthcare organisations should support and utilise iHV research to inform policy and practice.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-80_ pf-text-1"><strong>Leverage technology</strong> - Utilising compliance management software like ComplyPlus™ can help health visitors and organisations streamline their adherence to legislation and regulatory standards, ensuring high-quality care delivery.



















</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-82_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-83_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-84_ pf-heading-1-h3">Conclusion
